---
import "../styles/main.css"
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro"
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro"
import ThemeInit from "../components/ThemeInit.astro"
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="scroll-smooth">
<head><meta charset="UTF-8" /><ThemeInit /><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
<title>Learn Korean with Flashcards - Free App with TTS Pronunciation</title>
<meta name="description" content="Learn Korean vocabulary with free flashcards featuring TTS pronunciation and spaced repetition. Start with our Korean Basics deck. No account required." />
<link rel="canonical" href="https://fluentcards.org/learn-korean/" />
<meta property="og:title" content="Learn Korean with Flashcards - Free App" />
<meta property="og:description" content="Free Korean flashcard app with TTS pronunciation and spaced repetition." />
<meta property="og:url" content="https://fluentcards.org/learn-korean/" />
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
<script type="application/ld+json">{ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "WebPage", "name": "Learn Korean with Flashcards", "url": "https://fluentcards.org/learn-korean/" }</script>
<script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-4482389932723468" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body class="font-sans text-slate-700 bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark dark:text-slate-400 antialiased overflow-x-hidden">
<Nav currentPath="/learn-korean/" />
<main class="pt-32 pb-16 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center reveal-up">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Learn Korean with Flashcards</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Build your Korean vocabulary with smart flashcards featuring TTS pronunciation, FSRS spaced repetition, and a free Korean Basics deck. No account needed, works in your browser.</p>
    <a href="/app/" class="mt-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-primary text-white px-8 py-3.5 rounded-xl font-bold shadow-lg shadow-primary/25 hover:shadow-xl transition-all">Start Learning Korean Free</a>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-16 space-y-8">
    <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-surface-card rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 reveal-up">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-3">Korean Basics Deck</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">FluentCards includes a free Korean Basics deck with 35 essential vocabulary words covering greetings, common verbs, numbers, and everyday phrases. Each card includes the Korean spelling, English translation, and TTS audio for correct pronunciation. The deck is designed for absolute beginners who want to start speaking Korean immediately. Clone the deck in one click and begin your first review session without any setup or account creation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-surface-card rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 reveal-up delay-1">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-3">Korean Pronunciation with TTS</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Korean has sounds that do not exist in English, such as tense consonants and complex vowel combinations. Hearing correct pronunciation from the beginning is essential to avoid developing bad habits. FluentCards uses Microsoft Edge TTS to provide natural Korean pronunciation for every card. You can adjust the speech rate to match your listening level, slowing down difficult words and speeding up as your ear adjusts. Use the shadowing technique: listen to the TTS audio and repeat aloud immediately, matching the rhythm and intonation as closely as possible.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-surface-card rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 reveal-up delay-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-3">Spaced Repetition for Korean Vocabulary</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Korean vocabulary requires consistent review to move words from short-term to long-term memory. The FSRS spaced repetition algorithm in FluentCards automatically schedules reviews at the optimal time based on your individual performance. Words you find difficult appear more frequently, while words you know well appear less often. This adaptive approach reduces total study time while improving retention. Studies show that spaced repetition can increase long-term recall by up to 50% compared to traditional study methods.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-surface-card rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 reveal-up delay-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-3">Tips for Learning Korean</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Start by mastering Hangul, the Korean alphabet. Unlike Japanese or Chinese, Korean has a phonetic alphabet that can be learned in a few hours. Once you can read Hangul, focus on building vocabulary through flashcards while simultaneously studying basic grammar patterns. Korean sentence structure follows a subject-object-verb order, which is different from English. Create sentence cards in FluentCards that show full Korean sentences on the front with translations on the back to internalize this structure naturally.</p>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed mt-3">Consistency is the key to progress. Study for 15 to 20 minutes daily rather than cramming for hours once a week. The FluentCards streak tracker helps you maintain momentum, and the Discover section has starter decks to get you going immediately without any setup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

<h2>Getting Started with Korean</h2>
<p>FluentCards makes it easy to start learning Korean. When you open the app, you can immediately access the Korean Basics starter deck with 35 essential vocabulary words. Each card includes the Korean word, English translation, and TTS audio. The FSRS spaced repetition algorithm automatically schedules your reviews for maximum efficiency. Words you find difficult appear more frequently, while words you know fade into the background.</p>
<h2>Pronunciation and Listening</h2>
<p>FluentCards includes built-in TTS pronunciation that lets you hear each Korean word spoken naturally. Listen and repeat aloud to practice your pronunciation. Adjust the speech rate from slow to natural speed. Combine flashcard study with real-world exposure to Korean through podcasts, videos, and conversations for the fastest results.</p>
<h2>Building Your Vocabulary</h2>
<p>Study 15 to 20 minutes daily. Review all due cards and add 5 to 10 new words. At this pace you can learn over 1,000 words in three months. The streak tracker helps maintain momentum, and the FSRS algorithm ensures retention through optimally scheduled reviews.</p>

<p>Korean Basics starter deck gives you 35 essential Korean words with English translations and TTS audio. Korean has a phonetic alphabet that can be learned quickly, making vocabulary acquisition the main focus. FluentCards provides all the tools you need to build Korean vocabulary efficiently through spaced repetition, active recall, and consistent daily practice. The FSRS algorithm adapts to your memory and schedules reviews at optimal intervals. Start with the starter deck and expand with your own cards as you encounter new words in your studies. Whether you are learning for travel, work, or personal enrichment, FluentCards helps you make steady progress toward your Korean goals.</p><p>Consistent daily practice is the key to language learning success. Study for 15 to 20 minutes each day, complete all due reviews, and add 5 to 10 new vocabulary items. The streak tracker keeps you motivated, and the progress statistics show your improvements over time. With FluentCards, you have a complete language learning system that works on any device, anywhere, without requiring an account or subscription.</p><p>The combination of flashcards, TTS pronunciation, and spaced repetition creates a powerful learning environment that addresses reading comprehension, listening comprehension, and speaking ability simultaneously. By integrating these elements into a single seamless application, FluentCards helps you learn Korean more efficiently than traditional methods allow.</p>
<p>Korean is a fascinating language with a unique and scientifically designed alphabet called Hangul. Unlike the thousands of characters needed for Chinese or Japanese, Hangul consists of 24 basic letters that combine into syllabic blocks. This means you can learn to read Korean in just a few hours, making vocabulary acquisition the primary focus of your studies. FluentCards Korean Basics deck provides 35 essential words to get you started immediately. Each card includes Hangul spelling, English translation, and TTS audio for correct pronunciation.</p><p>Korean grammar follows a subject-object-verb structure that differs from English. Creating sentence cards in FluentCards helps you internalize this structure naturally. Include full Korean sentences on the front with translations on the back. As you review these sentences, your brain internalizes the word order patterns without needing to study grammar rules explicitly. Combine this with vocabulary cards for the fastest path to Korean conversational ability.</p>
<p>Korean speech levels are an important aspect of the language that reflect social relationships between speakers. Korean has multiple honorific levels that change verb endings and vocabulary choices. Creating flashcards for different speech levels helps you internalize which forms to use in various social contexts. The FluentCards TTS feature is particularly helpful for practicing speech levels because each level has distinct intonation patterns that are difficult to learn from text alone.</p>
</main>
<Footer />
<script>const o=new IntersectionObserver(e=>{e.forEach(e=>{e.isIntersecting&&e.target.classList.add("visible")})},{threshold:.08});document.querySelectorAll(".reveal-up").forEach(e=>o.observe(e));</script>
</body>
</html>
